Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.48,0:53:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this this There can be no hate,\N{\rChinese}这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这这可以没有仇
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.66,0:53:39.06,English,,0,0,0,,there can be no envy, there can be no blemishes within the nature of God.\N{\rChinese}有了恩惠，神的本性里就没有嫉妒，也没有瑕疵。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.60,0:53:41.28,English,,0,0,0,,All that\N{\rChinese}一切皆是如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.28,0:53:43.92,English,,0,0,0,,derives directly from this goodness is everlasting,\N{\rChinese}直接来自这永恒的善，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.22,0:53:47.96,English,,0,0,0,,since the seal of goodness impresses an imprint that never alters.\N{\rChinese}因为善的印记留下不变的烙印。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.38,0:53:49.66,English,,0,0,0,,So God,\N{\rChinese}于是上帝，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.04,0:53:53.10,English,,0,0,0,,when God creates, what he creates is also perfect.\N{\rChinese}当神创造时，他所创造的也同样完好。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.86,0:53:59.32,English,,0,0,0,,Only man's sin annuls man's liberty,\N{\rChinese}只有人的罪才消灭人的自由。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.60,0:54:02.30,English,,0,0,0,,makes him unlike the highest good, so that\N{\rChinese}使他与至善不同，以便
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.30,0:54:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,in him the brightness of his light is dim.\N{\rChinese}在他身上，他光的明亮变得黯淡。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.38,0:54:08.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So God is in us.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是上帝就在我们里面。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.56,0:54:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,God is the light that burns in us and allows us to love others.\N{\rChinese}上帝是燃烧在我们内的光，让我们能去爱他人。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.02,0:54:17.94,English,,0,0,0,,When we love others, the brightness burns brighter.\N{\rChinese}当我们去爱他人时，光亮更灿烂。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.34,0:54:19.90,English,,0,0,0,,The light burns brighter.\N{\rChinese}光亮更灿烂。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.40,0:54:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's how we celebrate God, by loving others.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是我们通过爱他人来庆祝上帝的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.28,0:54:27.50,English,,0,0,0,,We also have the freedom of the will.\N{\rChinese}我们也拥有意志的自由。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.66,0:54:30.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So these are the two things that God has given us.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是上帝赐给我们的两件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.22,0:54:34.94,English,,0,0,0,,Freedom to choose. Freedom to lead the lives we want to live,\N{\rChinese}自由选择。自由过我们想过的生活，以及爱与想象的力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.51,0:54:39.40,English,,0,0,0,,as well as the power to love and to imagine.\N{\rChinese}自由选择。自由过我们想过的生活，以及爱与想象的力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.94,0:54:43.70,English,,0,0,0,,But these things come into conflict when we choose to do bad.\N{\rChinese}但这些事物在我们选择做坏事时会相互冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.46,0:54:47.66,English,,0,0,0,,When we choose to disobey, when we choose to commit sin,\N{\rChinese}当我们选择不服从时，当我们选择犯罪时。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.86,0:54:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,we are turning away from God and therefore dampening the brightness in us.\N{\rChinese}我们正离开上帝，因而把我们内在的光亮抑制下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.26,0:54:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We are purposely stuffing out the flame in us.\N{\rChinese}好吧？我们有意把内在的火焰塞住。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.24,0:55:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,And man cannot regain his dignity,\N{\rChinese}而人若要恢复尊严，只有在罪空缺之处填补时才行得通
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.68,0:55:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,unless where sin left emptiness, man fills that\N{\rChinese}人若要恢复尊严，只有在罪空缺之处填补时才行得通
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.48,0:55:06.70,English,,0,0,0,,void with just amends for evil pleasure.\N{\rChinese}以仅补偿邪乐而空虚。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.92,0:55:10.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So when we commit sin, you must make amends.\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以当我们犯下罪时，你必须补偿。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.32,0:55:11.90,English,,0,0,0,,You must force yourself.\N{\rChinese}你必须自我强行。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.02,0:55:16.04,English,,0,0,0,,You must choose to go on the proper path and make amends.\N{\rChinese}你必须选择走正确的道路并补偿。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.10,0:55:22.78,English,,0,0,0,,But for when your nature sinned so\N{\rChinese}但当你的本性犯下罪时……
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.78,0:55:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,totally within its seed, then from these dignities,\N{\rChinese}完全在其种子之内，然后从这些尊贵之中，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.12,0:55:28.34,English,,0,0,0,,just as from paradise, that nature parted.\N{\rChinese}正如从天堂，那个本性分离。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.58,0:55:31.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Sometimes you could commit a sin that's so terrible,\N{\rChinese}好吧？有时你会犯下如此可怕的罪，光就离你而去。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.60,0:55:33.38,English,,0,0,0,,the light leaves you.\N{\rChinese}好吧？有时你会犯下如此可怕的罪，光就离你而去。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.32,0:55:38.78,English,,0,0,0,,And that's when we disobeyed God in the Garden of Eden.\N{\rChinese}那时我们在伊甸园里违背了上帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.60,0:55:42.64,English,,0,0,0,,That sin, the original sin, was so terrible\N{\rChinese}那罪，原罪，极其可怕。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.64,0:55:47.40,English,,0,0,0,,that Adam doomed all his progeny to darkness.\N{\rChinese}那亚当让他的后裔陷入黑暗。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.48,0:55:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.24,0:55:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,they could never be regained if you consider carefully by any way\N{\rChinese}他们若仔细考虑，若不经过这两座堡垒，便永不再得回。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.82,0:55:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,that did not pass across one of these two forts.\N{\rChinese}若不跨过这两座堡垒，便永不再得回。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.66,0:55:58.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So how do we forgive?\N{\rChinese}好吧？那我们怎么求赎？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.62,0:56:00.34,English,,0,0,0,,How do we ask for forgiveness?\N{\rChinese}我们怎么请求赎？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.72,0:56:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There are two possibilities. Either through nothing other than his mercy,\N{\rChinese}好吧？有两种可能。要么仅凭他的恩典。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.52,0:56:08.14,English,,0,0,0,,God had to pardon man, or of himself,\N{\rChinese}上帝必须赎回人，或赎回自己，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.50,0:56:11.04,English,,0,0,0,,man had to proffer payment for his father.\N{\rChinese}人必须为父亲提供报酬，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.30,0:56:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,So there are two ways for us to get that\N{\rChinese}于是我们有两种方式获得赎回
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.38,0:56:17.18,English,,0,0,0,,light back in us, to redeem ourselves in the eyes of God.\N{\rChinese}光回到我们心中，以在上帝眼中赎回自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.34,0:56:19.72,English,,0,0,0,,The first way is if God just forgives us.\N{\rChinese}第一种方式是上帝只赎回我们。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.78,0:56:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,If God says, I'm total,\N{\rChinese}如果上帝说，我完全……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.52,0:56:25.42,English,,0,0,0,,I'm perfect, I'm total perfect in this, I forgive you.\N{\rChinese}我完美，我在此完全完美，我赎你。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.48,0:56:26.98,English,,0,0,0,,Because that's what I do, I forgive you.\N{\rChinese}因为这就是我所做的，我赎你。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.54,0:56:29.34,English,,0,0,0,,To show mercy. That's one possibility.\N{\rChinese}以示恩。那是一个可能。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.90,0:56:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,But when he does that, the problem is we've learned nothing.\N{\rChinese}但当他这么做时，问题是我们没有学到什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.04,0:56:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,We haven't grown. Okay?\N{\rChinese}我们没有成长。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.66,0:56:41.84,English,,0,0,0,,Another possibility is if we figure\N{\rChinese}另一种可能是我们想出来。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.84,0:56:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,out a way to redeem ourselves.\N{\rChinese}出路去赎回自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.18,0:56:46.04,English,,0,0,0,,If we make amends.\N{\rChinese}若我们补偿。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.32,0:56:49.02,English,,0,0,0,,If we give God all the gold in the world.\N{\rChinese}若我们把世界上所有黄金都给上帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.70,0:56:52.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But because our crime was so\N{\rChinese}好的？但因为我们的罪行如此之大，因我们否认上帝之爱，所做之事无一能赎回我们之罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.62,0:56:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,great, because we denied the love of God, nothing we do,\N{\rChinese}因为我们的罪行如此之大，因我们否认上帝之爱，所做之事无一能赎回我们之罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.04,0:57:00.42,English,,0,0,0,,there's nothing we could give God that would redeem us from our sin.\N{\rChinese}因为我们的罪行如此之大，因我们否认上帝之爱，所做之事无一能赎回我们之罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.42,0:57:01.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's a conflict here.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是一个冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.96,0:57:05.14,English,,0,0,0,,That's a paradox. God cannot forgive us because if he did\N{\rChinese}那是个悖论。若上帝赦免我们，便不再有成长与学习。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.14,0:57:07.32,English,,0,0,0,,so, we would not grow and learn.\N{\rChinese}so, we would notgrow and learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.56,0:57:13.84,English,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing we can do to redeem ourselves in the eyes of God\N{\rChinese}好吧？但因为我们的罪行如此之大，所做之事无一能赎回我们之罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.84,0:57:15.90,English,,0,0,0,,because our crimes were so great. So that's the paradox.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是一个悖论。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.24,0:57:21.78,English,,0,0,0,,Man's limits could not recompensate for no obedience,\N{\rChinese}人的极限无法补偿无顺从的缺失，而他随后所献的谦逊也不足以补偿。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.88,0:57:24.72,English,,0,0,0,,no humility he offered later could have been so\N{\rChinese}人的极限无法补偿无顺从的缺失，随后他所献的谦逊也不足以补偿。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.72,0:57:29.18,English,,0,0,0,,deep that it could match the heights he meant to reach through disobedience.\N{\rChinese}深深的，他的失意能与他通过不顺从想要达到的高度相匹配。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.18,0:57:32.02,English,,0,0,0,,Man lacked the power to offer satisfaction by himself.\N{\rChinese}人类缺乏自我所能提供的满足之力。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.54,0:57:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,We want to kill God.\N{\rChinese}我们想杀上帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.70,0:57:35.98,English,,0,0,0,,That was the original sin.\N{\rChinese}那是最初的罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.14,0:57:39.22,English,,0,0,0,,We wanted to eat that fruit, become God, and\N{\rChinese}我们想吃那果实，成为上帝，且
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.22,0:57:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,then kill God and become God itself.\N{\rChinese}然后杀死上帝并成为上帝本身。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.72,0:57:44.84,English,,0,0,0,,That's the greatest crime. So how can you redeem yourself?\N{\rChinese}那是最大的罪。那你又怎么能自我赎呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.22,0:57:49.84,English,,0,0,0,,How can you ask for forgiveness if the crime is to kill God?\N{\rChinese}如果罪是杀上帝，你怎么能求赎呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.20,0:57:56.52,English,,0,0,0,,Right? For God showed greater generosity in giving his own self\N{\rChinese}对吧？因为上帝在自我奉献时表现出更大的慷慨。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.52,0:57:58.74,English,,0,0,0,,that men might be able to rise.\N{\rChinese}那样人们就能崛起。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.74,0:58:00.56,English,,0,0,0,,Than if he simply pardoned.\N{\rChinese}那如果他只是赦免。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.74,0:58:02.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for thousands of years,\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是千百年间，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.68,0:58:07.34,English,,0,0,0,,God had to think of a way to redeem us,\N{\rChinese}上帝必须想出一种办法来赎我们，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.40,0:58:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,to forgive us, but\N{\rChinese}再来赦我们，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.76,0:58:12.56,English,,0,0,0,,at the same time ensure we would not do anything like this ever again.\N{\rChinese}在同一时间，确保我们以后再也不会做类似的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.82,0:58:17.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the path he chose was to sacrifice himself.\N{\rChinese}好的？他选择的道路就是自我牺献。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.76,0:58:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,For every other means fell short of justice except\N{\rChinese}对其他手段都不足以实现正义，唯有那种方式——神之子在成道时自我降卑。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.96,0:58:26.86,English,,0,0,0,,the way whereby the Son of God humbled himself when he became incarnate.\N{\rChinese}the way whereby the Son of God humbled himself when he became incarnate.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.32,0:58:31.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So. I'm going to use a metaphor to explain this idea.\N{\rChinese}好的？那么。我打算用个比喻来说明这个想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.48,0:58:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,It's a very, it's not a great metaphor, but\N{\rChinese}这比喻很简单，算不上大比喻，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.32,0:58:38.12,English,,0,0,0,,I think this will illustrate what Beatrice is saying here about God.\N{\rChinese}我觉得这能说明贝娅特丽丝在这里说的关于上帝的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.70,0:58:40.10,English,,0,0,0,,Let's just say I have a daughter named Eve.\N{\rChinese}就说我有个叫伊娃的女儿吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.34,0:58:42.78,English,,0,0,0,,I have a favorite dog named Johnny.\N{\rChinese}我有一只叫约翰尼的狗。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.88,0:58:44.16,English,,0,0,0,,I love Johnny and I love Eve.\N{\rChinese}我爱约翰尼，也爱伊娃。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.22,0:58:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,I love both. Okay? And I say to Eve,\N{\rChinese}我两者都爱。好了？然后我对伊娃说，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.48,0:58:49.82,English,,0,0,0,,Johnny is my favorite dog.\N{\rChinese}约翰尼是我最爱的狗。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.16,0:58:51.82,English,,0,0,0,,You're my favorite, favorite daughter.\N{\rChinese}你是我最爱的女儿。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.14,0:58:56.84,English,,0,0,0,,I love you both. Eve, because she's young and she's stupid.\N{\rChinese}我两者都爱。伊娃，因为她年轻又笨。”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.84,0:59:00.00,English,,0,0,0,,She decides I only want my father to love me.\N{\rChinese}她决定我只想让父亲爱我。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.08,0:59:02.84,English,,0,0,0,,So Eve purposely kills my dog, Johnny.\N{\rChinese}于是伊娃故意杀死我的狗约翰尼。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.56,0:59:06.74,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Now, what do I do?\N{\rChinese}一切都好？现在，我该怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.14,0:59:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,I'm Eve's father. If I just say, Eve, don't worry about it.\N{\rChinese}我是伊娃的父亲。如果我只是说，伊娃，别担心。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.36,0:59:12.78,English,,0,0,0,,You're young. It was a mistake.\N{\rChinese}你还年轻，犯了个错误。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.32,0:59:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,Eve is probably going to go hurt someone else.\N{\rChinese}伊娃大概会去伤害别人。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.40,0:59:17.16,English,,0,0,0,,Right? I have to teach her a lesson.\N{\rChinese}对吗？我得给她上一课。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.88,0:59:23.10,English,,0,0,0,,But if I hit her or I punish her,\N{\rChinese}但如果我打她或惩罚她，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.26,0:59:26.82,English,,0,0,0,,then that might suggest to Eve, I'm going to punish her.\N{\rChinese}然后这可能会让伊娃觉得，我要惩罚她。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.82,0:59:29.32,English,,0,0,0,,I don't really love her. It doesn't make sense.\N{\rChinese}我并不是真的爱她，这没什么意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.38,0:59:32.00,English,,0,0,0,,That's a paradox here. That's a conflict. And so\N{\rChinese}那是个悖论。那是个冲突。于是…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.00,0:59:34.44,English,,0,0,0,,what I choose to do after many weeks\N{\rChinese}我在许多周后选择做的事…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.44,0:59:37.50,English,,0,0,0,,of intense thinking is I choose\N{\rChinese}强烈思考之后，我决定为伊娃惩罚自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.50,0:59:40.74,English,,0,0,0,,to punish myself on behalf of Eve.\N{\rChinese}好的？我拿起一根棍子。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.30,0:59:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? I take a bat and\N{\rChinese}Okay? I take a bat and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.54,0:59:46.12,English,,0,0,0,,I hit myself or I take a whip and I hit myself and\N{\rChinese}我自打自己或自鞭自打自己并且
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.12,0:59:48.40,English,,0,0,0,,my hand is bleeding and Eve watches this.\N{\rChinese}我的手流血，伊娃在看着
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.42,0:59:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,And you can see that when\N{\rChinese}你可以看到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.96,0:59:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,Eve sees this, she has to cry.\N{\rChinese}伊娃看到后哭了起来。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.82,0:59:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,She has to cry and feel sorry.\N{\rChinese}她哭了又感到抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.82,0:59:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,She has to feel remorse for what she did.\N{\rChinese}她为所做之事感到悔悟。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.04,1:00:03.62,English,,0,0,0,,And she also cries because she knows I truly love her.\N{\rChinese}她也哭了，因为她知道我真的爱她。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.48,1:00:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So that's what features is saying here.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这就是特征在这里说的。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.80,1:00:09.22,English,,0,0,0,,God loves us so much that\N{\rChinese}上帝如此爱我们，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.22,1:00:14.42,English,,0,0,0,,he's willing to do everything in order to teach us to be better human beings.\N{\rChinese}他愿意做一切事来教我们成为更好的人。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.64,1:00:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the power of God.\N{\rChinese}好？这就是上帝的力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.10,1:00:20.42,English,,0,0,0,,All right. All right.\N{\rChinese}好的。好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.46,1:00:25.12,English,,0,0,0,,So the conversation continues and this story makes sense.\N{\rChinese}于是对话继续，故事也就有了意义。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.12,1:00:27.56,English,,0,0,0,,But it's also going to create a lot of problems.\N{\rChinese}但它也会带来不少问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.86,1:00:31.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? One major problem is if God created us\N{\rChinese}好？一个大问题是如果上帝造了我们…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.14,1:00:35.12,English,,0,0,0,,and God loves us,\N{\rChinese}而上帝爱我们，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.32,1:00:38.20,English,,0,0,0,,why are we making mistakes?\N{\rChinese}为什么我们会犯错？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.94,1:00:41.30,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we dying?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么会死去？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.54,1:00:43.02,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we in pain? Okay?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么会痛？好？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.10,1:00:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,And this is what features says.\N{\rChinese}这就是特征所说的。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.86,1:00:47.94,English,,0,0,0,,You say, I see that water set fire\N{\rChinese}你说，我看见水点燃。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.94,1:00:51.66,English,,0,0,0,,and ear and earth and all that they compose come to corruption\N{\rChinese}耳朔和地球以及它们所组成的一切都归于腐败
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.66,1:00:53.00,English,,0,0,0,,and endure so briefly.\N{\rChinese}并且短暂地承受。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.12,1:00:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So in this world there is death, there is dying, there is pain, there is suffering.\N{\rChinese}好了？所以在这个世界里有死亡，有逝亡，有痛苦，有苦难。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.92,1:00:58.60,English,,0,0,0,,Why is that? And\N{\rChinese}为什么会这样？而且
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.60,1:01:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,yet these two were things created if what has been said above is true,\N{\rChinese}于是这两件事若前面所说成立，则已被创造
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.46,1:01:06.42,English,,0,0,0,,then these things never should be subject to corruption.\N{\rChinese}于是这些事物就不应受腐败。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.88,1:01:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,If whatever God creates is perfect,\N{\rChinese}若上帝所造皆为完好。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.88,1:01:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,then things shouldn't die.\N{\rChinese}于是事物就不应死亡。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.74,1:01:15.60,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Brother,\N{\rChinese}好了？兄弟，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.60,1:01:18.96,English,,0,0,0,,the angels in the pure country where\N{\rChinese}天使在你现在所在的纯净之国，已可说是按其全然而被造。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.96,1:01:22.84,English,,0,0,0,,you are now, these may be said to be created as they are in all their being.\N{\rChinese}天使在你现在所在的纯净之国，已可说是按其全然而被造。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.28,1:01:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Yes, it is true that God created everything in this world,\N{\rChinese}好的？是的，确实上帝造了这世界的一切事物。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.58,1:01:28.40,English,,0,0,0,,but there's a problem.\N{\rChinese}但有个问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.46,1:01:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,There's a difference. Whereas the elements that\N{\rChinese}有区别。虽然那些元素
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.44,1:01:33.98,English,,0,0,0,,you have mentioned, as well as those things that\N{\rChinese}你提到的，以及那些事物
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.98,1:01:37.78,English,,0,0,0,,are made from them, received their form from a created power,\N{\rChinese}它们由此而成，形态由造物之力所获，所含物质正如星辰之中所造，赋形之力亦已被造。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.42,1:01:44.12,English,,0,0,0,,the matter they contain had been created just as within the stars\N{\rChinese}它们由此而成，形态由造物之力所获，所含物质正如星辰之中所造，赋形之力亦已被造。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.12,1:01:47.46,English,,0,0,0,,that wheel around them, the power to give form had been created.\N{\rChinese}它们由此而成，形态由造物之力所获，所含物质正如星辰之中所造，赋形之力亦已被造。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.58,1:01:52.78,English,,0,0,0,,The rays and motion of the holy light draw forth the soul of every animal\N{\rChinese}神圣之光的光束与运动，提拉出每只动物的灵魂
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.78,1:01:57.14,English,,0,0,0,,and every being. If God\N{\rChinese}并且每个存在。如果上帝创建了这个世界，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.14,1:02:01.38,English,,0,0,0,,created this world,\N{\rChinese}created this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.98,1:02:06.00,English,,0,0,0,,this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world,\N{\rChinese}这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.00,1:02:09.52,English,,0,0,0,,this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world, this world,\N{\rChinese}这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界这个世界
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.52,1:02:12.42,English,,0,0,0,,this world, this world, this world, this world,\N{\rChinese}这个世界，这个世界，这个世界，这个世界，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.68,1:02:16.38,English,,0,0,0,,this world, this world, this world,\N{\rChinese}这个世界，这个世界，这个世界，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.88,1:02:19.20,English,,0,0,0,,this world, this world,\N{\rChinese}这个世界，这个世界，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.82,1:02:24.02,English,,0,0,0,,this world, new creations can come out, okay?\N{\rChinese}这个世界，新的创造可以出现，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.84,1:02:27.52,English,,0,0,0,,When an animal dies,\N{\rChinese}当动物死亡时，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.80,1:02:30.42,English,,0,0,0,,the atoms break away and then a new form comes into being.\N{\rChinese}原子分离，随后出现新的形态。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.54,1:02:34.18,English,,0,0,0,,That's the law of the universe. So that's perfect, but not the animals and plants are perfect.\N{\rChinese}那是宇宙的规律。所以它是完美的，但动物和植物并非完美。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.92,1:02:40.36,English,,0,0,0,,But your life is breathed forth immediately by the chief good\N{\rChinese}但你的生命立即由至善所吹出。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.36,1:02:44.18,English,,0,0,0,,who so enamors it of his own self that it desires him always.\N{\rChinese}谁把它自己迷住，便总想它。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.54,1:02:48.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so now the question then is, if animals and plants aren't perfect,\N{\rChinese}好了，现在的问题是，如果动物和植物不完美，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.54,1:02:54.26,English,,0,0,0,,what are humans then? So,\N{\rChinese}人类又是什么？那么，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.26,1:02:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,okay, and this is what she says.\N{\rChinese}好了，这就是她说的，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.26,1:03:02.06,English,,0,0,0,,So reasoning, you can also can deduce your resurrection.\N{\rChinese}于是推理，你也可以推断你的复活。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.24,1:03:06.50,English,,0,0,0,,You need but remember the way in which your human flesh was fashioned\N{\rChinese}你只需记住你人类肉体成形的方式
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.94,1:03:08.94,English,,0,0,0,,when both of the first parents were created.\N{\rChinese}当第一对父母被造时的那一刻
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.16,1:03:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is the trick.\N{\rChinese}好了，这就是诀窍。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.08,1:03:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,You have to remember this. Animals\N{\rChinese}你要记住这一点。动物
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.50,1:03:17.70,English,,0,0,0,,and plants are created from the laws of the universe which God created.\N{\rChinese}植物也是由宇宙规律所造，正是上帝所造。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.48,1:03:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,Angels are created by God himself.\N{\rChinese}天使由上帝亲自所造。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.96,1:03:27.26,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore the angels are perfect. We humans have a dual nature.\N{\rChinese}于是天使完好无缺。我们人类有双重本性。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.70,1:03:30.48,English,,0,0,0,,We are both created from the laws of the universe and\N{\rChinese}我们同样是由宇宙规律造就的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.48,1:03:33.48,English,,0,0,0,,we are both created by God itself, all right?\N{\rChinese}我们同样是上帝亲自所造，没错吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.28,1:03:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,Because when God created Adam,\N{\rChinese}因为当上帝造亚当时，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.58,1:03:41.28,English,,0,0,0,,God created him from out of dust, okay?\N{\rChinese}上帝把他从尘土中造出来，没错吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.48,1:03:45.04,English,,0,0,0,,But then what God did was breathe life into him.\N{\rChinese}然后上帝所做的就是给他注入生命。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.80,1:03:49.78,English,,0,0,0,,So the essence of God is within Adam and therefore us.\N{\rChinese}于是神的本质在亚当之中，也在我们之中。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.88,1:03:52.74,English,,0,0,0,,Our bodies are mortal.\N{\rChinese}我们的身体是有形的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.74,1:03:54.50,English,,0,0,0,,Our souls are immortal. But our souls are immortal.\N{\rChinese}我们的灵魂是永生的。我们的灵魂是永生的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.00,1:03:59.32,English,,0,0,0,,Our souls have the essence of God, which is love.\N{\rChinese}我们的灵魂拥有神的本质，即爱。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.56,1:04:03.12,English,,0,0,0,,The more we love, the more the light burns in us.\N{\rChinese}我们越爱，内心的光芒越燃起。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.98,1:04:05.84,English,,0,0,0,,And as light burns in us,\N{\rChinese}光芒在我们心中燃起时，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.58,1:04:09.70,English,,0,0,0,,it will allow for our resurrection,\N{\rChinese}它将为我们的复活提供机会，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.12,1:04:12.16,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Because\N{\rChinese}好了？因为
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.16,1:04:15.54,English,,0,0,0,,the matter will regenerate.\N{\rChinese}事物将会再生。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.62,1:04:18.30,English,,0,0,0,,The soul is eternal, okay?\N{\rChinese}灵魂永存，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.42,1:04:20.88,English,,0,0,0,,So that's what Dante is saying here.\N{\rChinese}这就是但丁在这里说的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.88,1:04:24.48,English,,0,0,0,,The best way to celebrate God is by loving others.\N{\rChinese}最好的方式是通过爱他人来庆祝上帝。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.64,1:04:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,When you love others, you are activating your imagination.\N{\rChinese}当你爱他人时，你就激活了你的想象力。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.12,1:04:31.50,English,,0,0,0,,You are learning wisdom.\N{\rChinese}你正在学习智慧。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.72,1:04:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,You are gaining experience. And that\N{\rChinese}你正在获得经验。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.54,1:04:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,will only cause the light to grow, okay?\N{\rChinese}只会让光更亮，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.14,1:04:41.54,English,,0,0,0,,So even though, going back to the story of Eve\N{\rChinese}于是即使回到伊甸的故事和我的狗，虽然我自伤自痛，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.54,1:04:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,and my dog, even though I'm hurting myself,\N{\rChinese}and my dog, even though I'm hurting myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.88,1:04:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,okay, I am using my tremendous imagination in order to come up with this plan,\N{\rChinese}好的，我正用我巨大的想象力来构思这个计划，以此来挽回自己，好的？以此来挽回我的女儿。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.70,1:04:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,in order to redeem myself, okay? To redeem my daughter.\N{\rChinese}因为这份想象力，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.82,1:04:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,And because of this imagination,\N{\rChinese}And because of this imagination,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.78,1:04:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,I'm developing wisdom.\N{\rChinese}我正在培养智慧。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.30,1:04:58.58,English,,0,0,0,,And this light in me grows stronger.\N{\rChinese}而我内在的光芒愈发光。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.90,1:05:01.80,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So that's the purpose of life.\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是人生的目的。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.00,1:05:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,The purpose of life is to celebrate God\N{\rChinese}生命的目的就是庆祝上帝
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.82,1:05:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,by celebrating God in you.\N{\rChinese}通过在你身中庆祝上帝
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.64,1:05:13.14,English,,0,0,0,,By loving someone else so wholeheartedly that your imagination,\N{\rChinese}用全心去爱他人，使你的想象力
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.54,1:05:16.58,English,,0,0,0,,your wisdom, grows and grows so that\N{\rChinese}你的智慧愈发光，直到
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.58,1:05:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,your soul becomes eternal.\N{\rChinese}你的灵魂变得永恒。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.88,1:05:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,When it becomes eternal, it will always be resurrected in the world.\N{\rChinese}当它变得永恒时，它将永远在世界中复活。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.64,1:05:27.68,English,,0,0,0,,And your soul will remember the love inside you,\N{\rChinese}你的灵魂会记住内在的爱，并且会不断成长，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.76,1:05:30.80,English,,0,0,0,,and it will continue to grow and grow, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是上帝造我们的原因。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.12,1:05:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,This is why God created us.\N{\rChinese}This is why Godcreated us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.78,1:05:36.18,English,,0,0,0,,Because if God, if you're perfect, okay, if you're perfect,\N{\rChinese}因为如果上帝，如果你完美，好的，如果你完美，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.48,1:05:39.72,English,,0,0,0,,you are incapable of imagination by definition, right?\N{\rChinese}你按定义就没有想象力，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.76,1:05:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,Because you can make no mistakes. Because we are the dual nature,\N{\rChinese}因为你不会犯错。因为我们是双重本性，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.40,1:05:47.74,English,,0,0,0,,we are both body and soul, we can make mistakes.\N{\rChinese}我们既是身体又是灵魂，能犯错。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.02,1:05:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,We can err. We can err.\N{\rChinese}我们能犯错。我们能犯错。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.00,1:05:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,And in this process, we develop experience and\N{\rChinese}在这个过程中，我们积累经验。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.12,1:05:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,wisdom, which allows us to love and to have imagination,\N{\rChinese}智慧，让我们能爱与想象，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.90,1:05:58.64,English,,0,0,0,,and to have wisdom, all right?\N{\rChinese}以及拥有智慧，一切都好？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.32,1:06:02.36,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.36,1:06:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,let me use an everyday example that you've experienced in order to illustrate this point.\N{\rChinese}让我用一个你亲身经历过的日常例子来说明这一点。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.52,1:06:10.10,English,,0,0,0,,Let's think about two teachers, a teacher who\N{\rChinese}我们来想想两位老师，一位老师……
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.10,1:06:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,loves his or her students, and a teacher who\N{\rChinese}……又是一位老师……
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.20,1:06:15.12,English,,0,0,0,,does not love his or her students, okay?\N{\rChinese}不爱自己的学生，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.20,1:06:17.84,English,,0,0,0,,What's the difference? All right, so there are three major differences.\N{\rChinese}有什么区别？好，三点主要区别是：
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.24,1:06:21.44,English,,0,0,0,,The teacher who loves students, or is asking himself or herself,\N{\rChinese}那位爱学生的老师，或者他/她自己在问自己，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.64,1:06:23.72,English,,0,0,0,,are my students learning in my class?\N{\rChinese}我的学生在我的课上学习吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.84,1:06:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,Are they growing as people?\N{\rChinese}他们在成长为人吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.58,1:06:29.56,English,,0,0,0,,Whereas another teacher might be like, are my students getting good grades?\N{\rChinese}而另一位老师可能会问：我的学生拿到好成绩了吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.92,1:06:32.16,English,,0,0,0,,All he or she cares about are test scores, right?\N{\rChinese}他/她只关心的是考试成绩，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.36,1:06:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,That's the first major difference.\N{\rChinese}这就是第一个主要区别。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.22,1:06:38.02,English,,0,0,0,,The first teacher who loves you cares about what is happening inside you.\N{\rChinese}第一位爱你的老师关心的是你内在发生的事。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.12,1:06:40.74,English,,0,0,0,,What, the teacher who\N{\rChinese}什么，那个老师只关心让父母满意，没事吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.74,1:06:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,doesn't love you only cares about pleasing parents, okay?\N{\rChinese}第二个区别是这个。那个爱你的老师在问，…
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.30,1:06:48.82,English,,0,0,0,,Second difference is this. The teacher who loves you are asking,\N{\rChinese}Second difference is this. The teacher who loves you are asking,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.82,1:06:50.44,English,,0,0,0,,are my students working hard?\N{\rChinese}我的学生们在努力吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.38,1:06:53.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, because only by working hard can you learn.\N{\rChinese}好的，只有努力学习才能学会。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.00,1:06:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,The second teacher is asking, do students like me, okay?\N{\rChinese}第二位老师在问，学生们像我一样吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.56,1:07:02.14,English,,0,0,0,,The teacher wants you to write a good evaluation at the end of semester, okay?\N{\rChinese}老师想让你在学期末写一份好评语，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.58,1:07:05.72,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And then if you write a good evaluation,\N{\rChinese}对吗？然后如果你写了一份好评语，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.24,1:07:09.88,English,,0,0,0,,the teacher might get a raise or some reward, right?\N{\rChinese}老师可能会得到加薪或奖励，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.38,1:07:13.12,English,,0,0,0,,And then the last difference, and this is the most important difference, is this.\N{\rChinese}然后最后一个区别，这个区别最重要，便是这样。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.28,1:07:17.82,English,,0,0,0,,A good teacher who loves you is always asking, am I growing personally and professionally?\N{\rChinese}一位爱你的好老师总是问：我个人和专业上是否在成长？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.82,1:07:19.32,English,,0,0,0,,Am I growing as a person?\N{\rChinese}我作为一个人是否在成长？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.04,1:07:23.32,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Because if you're growing, then I'm growing.\N{\rChinese}好的？因为你在成长，我也在成长。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.50,1:07:25.26,English,,0,0,0,,And if I'm growing, then you're growing.\N{\rChinese}如果我在成长，你也在成长。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.14,1:07:28.18,English,,0,0,0,,That's the power of love, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是爱的力量，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.28,1:07:30.70,English,,0,0,0,,When you love others, you're actually loving yourself.\N{\rChinese}当你爱别人时，实际上就是在爱自己。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.24,1:07:33.88,English,,0,0,0,,And that's how God designed it.\N{\rChinese}这就是上帝的设计。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.10,1:07:38.34,English,,0,0,0,,But if you're a teacher who does not love, then you're always asking,\N{\rChinese}如果你是个不爱人的老师，那你就总是在问，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.50,1:07:40.00,English,,0,0,0,,how much money am I making?\N{\rChinese}我赚了多少钱？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.16,1:07:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,That's how you measure your success in life.\N{\rChinese}这就是你衡量人生成功的方式。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.50,1:07:45.42,English,,0,0,0,,Am I making a lot of money? If I'm making millions of dollars a year,\N{\rChinese}我赚了很多钱吗？如果我一年赚上百万美元，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.50,1:07:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,then that means I'm the best teacher in China, okay?\N{\rChinese}那么这就意味着我是中国最好的老师，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.82,1:07:50.60,English,,0,0,0,,But a really good teacher who's capable of love,\N{\rChinese}但真正优秀的老师能做到爱，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.72,1:07:54.02,English,,0,0,0,,who loves teaching and who loves his or her students,\N{\rChinese}他/她爱教学，也爱他的学生们。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.16,1:07:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,is always asking, am I growing?\N{\rChinese}我一直在问，我自己在成长吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.40,1:07:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,Because if I'm growing, then I know my students are growing.\N{\rChinese}因为如果我在成长，那我就知道我的学生也在成长。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.88,1:08:02.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好的？那么
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.12,1:08:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,that's what Dante is saying here about love.\N{\rChinese}那就是但丁在这里说的关于爱的内容。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.48,1:08:08.52,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning that we have intuition.\N{\rChinese}也就是说我们有直觉。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.46,1:08:12.52,English,,0,0,0,,We have the power to know truth for ourselves\N{\rChinese}我们有能力自己知道真理。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.52,1:08:15.28,English,,0,0,0,,because God made us this way.\N{\rChinese}因为上帝让我们如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.56,1:08:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。那么
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.44,1:08:22.90,English,,0,0,0,,something I want you to remember\N{\rChinese}我想让你记住的事是
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.90,1:08:25.46,English,,0,0,0,,from this class is the\N{\rChinese}从这门课得到的是
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.46,1:08:29.48,English,,0,0,0,,Italian Renaissance was really just another,\N{\rChinese}意大利文艺复兴实际上只是另一种
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.66,1:08:32.80,English,,0,0,0,,it's reimagining the Greek civilization,\N{\rChinese}它重新想象了希腊文明，
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.34,1:08:34.40,English,,0,0,0,,okay? And\N{\rChinese}好的？还有
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.40,1:08:40.00,English,,0,0,0,,these are the two major periods of tremendous creativity in Western Europe.\N{\rChinese}这些是西欧两大创意高峰期。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.58,1:08:45.16,English,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's look at the similarities to understand how creativity happened.\N{\rChinese}好了，先看相似点，理解创意如何产生。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.16,1:08:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,What happens in civilization. Okay, so\N{\rChinese}文明中发生了什么。好了，先说第一个相似点。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.56,1:08:52.06,English,,0,0,0,,the first similarity is classical\N{\rChinese}第一个相似点是古典希腊。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.06,1:08:54.58,English,,0,0,0,,Greece had open cooperative competition, okay?\N{\rChinese}古典希腊有开放的协作竞争。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.68,1:08:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,So ideas could flow freely.\N{\rChinese}于是思想可以自由流动。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.26,1:08:58.98,English,,0,0,0,,That's the first major similarity.\N{\rChinese}这就是第一个主要相似点。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.32,1:09:02.80,English,,0,0,0,,Second major similarity is in classical Greece,\N{\rChinese}第二个主要相似点是古典希腊。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.00,1:09:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,they transitioned from Linear B, which is very complicated,\N{\rChinese}他们从非常复杂的线性B文字转向字母表，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.32,1:09:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,idiographic language to the alphabet, okay?\N{\rChinese}字母表只把口语转写成文字。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.80,1:09:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,The alphabet just transcribes the written, the spoken word into the written word.\N{\rChinese}The alphabet just transcribes the written, the spoken word into the written word.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.56,1:09:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,This allows for massive literacy\N{\rChinese}这使得古希腊的文盲率大幅提升，知识得以大规模传播。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.88,1:09:19.66,English,,0,0,0,,and the transfusion of knowledge in Greece.\N{\rChinese}并且，若要成为真正的创意社会，关键在于……
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.92,1:09:22.98,English,,0,0,0,,And the idea here is if you are truly to be a creative society,\N{\rChinese}And the idea here is if you aretruly to be a creative society,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.24,1:09:24.86,English,,0,0,0,,you must be egalitarian.\N{\rChinese}你必须是平等的。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.16,1:09:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,You must allow anyone to learn,\N{\rChinese}你必须让任何人都能学习，
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.26,1:09:31.92,English,,0,0,0,,everyone to express his or her ideas,\N{\rChinese}每个人都能表达自己的想法。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.22,1:09:33.50,English,,0,0,0,,which is what the Renaissance did, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是文艺复兴所做的事，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.44,1:09:37.26,English,,0,0,0,,The Italian Renaissance was supported by the fact that\N{\rChinese}意大利文艺复兴得以此为支撑，原因是……
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.26,1:09:40.32,English,,0,0,0,,they transitioned from Latin to the vernacular, the spoken language.\N{\rChinese}他们从拉丁语转向方言，即口语。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.60,1:09:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,It was Dante who allowed the transition to Latin.\N{\rChinese}是但丁让这一转变成了拉丁语。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.56,1:09:48.60,English,,0,0,0,,to happen, okay? Dante purposefully chose not to write in Latin,\N{\rChinese}发生了，明白吗？但丁有意地选择不写拉丁语，
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.74,1:09:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,even though Latin was the official language of the intellectual class in Europe at this time.\N{\rChinese}即便拉丁语是当时欧洲知识阶层的官方语言。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.78,1:09:56.42,English,,0,0,0,,He purposely chose to write in Tuscan, which is a local language.\N{\rChinese}他专门选择用托斯卡语写作，这是一种地方语言。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.64,1:09:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,And because he did that, he made Tuscan, first of all,\N{\rChinese}因为他这么做，托斯卡语首先成为意大利的官方语言，至今仍被使用。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.60,1:10:04.36,English,,0,0,0,,the official language of Italy, they still speak it today, but it also makes the line comedy accessible\N{\rChinese}这也让戏剧更易被大众理解。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.00,1:10:07.84,English,,0,0,0,,to common people, which was the intention, okay?\N{\rChinese}给普通人听，正是意图，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.08,1:10:11.86,English,,0,0,0,,And the third similarity, and this is the most important,\N{\rChinese}第三点相似，且最重要的是，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.56,1:10:16.72,English,,0,0,0,,the perfect storm of factors don't really matter\N{\rChinese}完美的因素风暴并不重要
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.62,1:10:20.18,English,,0,0,0,,unless you have a great poet,\N{\rChinese}如果你没有一位伟大的诗人，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.40,1:10:21.84,English,,0,0,0,,a great thinker,\N{\rChinese}一位伟大的思想家，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.88,1:10:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,a great intellectual to create the spark to ignite your civilization,\N{\rChinese}一位伟大的知识分子来点燃你们的文明
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.44,1:10:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So in Greece, they had Homer,\N{\rChinese}好的？在希腊，他们有荷马，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.68,1:10:32.96,English,,0,0,0,,and today we can think of Homer as the father of civilization.\N{\rChinese}今天我们可以把荷马当作文明之父。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.46,1:10:37.16,English,,0,0,0,,In the Italian Renaissance, you had Dante.\N{\rChinese}在意大利文艺复兴时期，你有但丁。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.32,1:10:39.54,English,,0,0,0,,You can think of him as the father of modernity.\N{\rChinese}你可以把他当作现代性的父亲。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.68,1:10:42.74,English,,0,0,0,,The values that he creates, the values that\N{\rChinese}他创造的价值观， 他所表达的价值观， 他在喜剧中所拥有的价值观将成为现代性的基础。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.74,1:10:47.90,English,,0,0,0,,he expresses, the values that he has in the line comedy will become the basis for modernity,\N{\rChinese}he expresses, the values that he has in the line comedy will become the basis for modernity,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.96,1:10:51.08,English,,0,0,0,,especially the idea of individuality, of humanism, right?\N{\rChinese}尤其是个体性、人的主义的观念，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.34,1:10:56.00,English,,0,0,0,,What is an individual? An individual is someone who celebrates himself\N{\rChinese}个体是什么？个体是自我庆祝的人，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.40,1:11:00.98,English,,0,0,0,,and pursues his or her curiosity to explore the world\N{\rChinese}他或她追随好奇去探世界
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.98,1:11:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,and in this process create goodness in the world,\N{\rChinese}并在此过程中在世界中创造善良，并创造真理与美感。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.36,1:11:08.96,English,,0,0,0,,to create truth and beauty. This is the idea that will underpin the Renaissance\N{\rChinese}这就是支撑文艺复兴的理念，也仍是西方现代性与现代世界的基石。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.30,1:11:12.90,English,,0,0,0,,and which still underpins Western modernity and the modern world.\N{\rChinese}and which still underpins Western modernity and the modern world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.88,1:11:20.44,English,,0,0,0,,So, what is the ultimate message?\N{\rChinese}那么，最终的意思是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.50,1:11:26.16,English,,0,0,0,,The ultimate message is the ultimate secret of the universe.\N{\rChinese}最终的意思就是宇宙的终极秘密。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.26,1:11:27.56,English,,0,0,0,,I want you to remember, okay?\N{\rChinese}我想让你记住，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.62,1:11:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,And both Homer and Dante expressed this in their poetry.\N{\rChinese}并且荷马与但丁都在诗中表达了这一点。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.58,1:11:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,It's this. Love is the unifying force of the universe,\N{\rChinese}这就是了。爱是宇宙的统一力量，
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.14,1:11:37.10,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Love is God.\N{\rChinese}好吧？爱即是上帝。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.26,1:11:40.94,English,,0,0,0,,God is love. It's what unites everyone, okay?\N{\rChinese}上帝是爱。它把大家统一在一起，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.04,1:11:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,By loving someone else, you can become that person.\N{\rChinese}通过爱别人，你可以成为那个人。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.46,1:11:45.18,English,,0,0,0,,So, you can become that person. That person can become you.\N{\rChinese}于是，你就能成为那个人。那个人又能成为你。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.40,1:11:49.80,English,,0,0,0,,And the imagination is the animating force, okay?\N{\rChinese}并且想象是动能的力量，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.90,1:11:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,What gives life to the world is not God, but our imagination.\N{\rChinese}给世界生命的不是上帝，而是我们的想象。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.12,1:11:56.84,English,,0,0,0,,By imagining the world, the world becomes alive.\N{\rChinese}通过想象世界，世界就变得有生气。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.18,1:11:58.56,English,,0,0,0,,So, the greater our imagination,\N{\rChinese}于是，想象越大，想象就越有生气。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.96,1:12:01.48,English,,0,0,0,,the more alive our imagination becomes.\N{\rChinese}而这点在画中最直观地表现出来。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.88,1:12:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,And this idea is most visually expressed in the painting,\N{\rChinese}And this idea is most visually expressed in the painting,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.76,1:12:10.62,English,,0,0,0,,The Creation of Adam, by Michelangelo, okay?\N{\rChinese}《创世亚当》由米开朗创作，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.12,1:12:12.46,English,,0,0,0,,This is Michelangelo.\N{\rChinese}这就是米开朗。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.14,1:12:14.44,English,,0,0,0,,The Creation of Adam.\N{\rChinese}《创世亚当》。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.82,1:12:18.62,English,,0,0,0,,And so, this goes back to the story of how God created Adam.\N{\rChinese}于是，这回到上帝创造亚当的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.46,1:12:21.92,English,,0,0,0,,God created Adam out of dust, and\N{\rChinese}上帝用尘土造亚当，且……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.92,1:12:25.62,English,,0,0,0,,he breathed the essence of life into Adam, okay?\N{\rChinese}并把生命的精气吹入亚当。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.12,1:12:30.46,English,,0,0,0,,Now, there are two ways of looking at this painting, okay?\N{\rChinese}现在，有两种方式来看这幅画，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.66,1:12:32.92,English,,0,0,0,,There are two ways of understanding the title, The Creation of Adam.\N{\rChinese}有两种方式来理解标题《创世亚当》。”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.18,1:12:36.38,English,,0,0,0,,You can first understand it in the typical way, which\N{\rChinese}你可以先按典型方式理解，……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.38,1:12:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,is that God created Adam, and that they are equals, okay?\N{\rChinese}是的，神造了亚当，且他们是平等的，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.18,1:12:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,You can see that these two worlds, the creation of Adam, and God, they're almost equal.\N{\rChinese}你可以看到这两个世界，亚当的创造和神，几乎是平等的。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.20,1:12:47.46,English,,0,0,0,,We are equal to God. But then you can change perspective,\N{\rChinese}我们与神平等。但随后你可以换个视角。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.62,1:12:49.80,English,,0,0,0,,and you can say, the creation of Adam really means\N{\rChinese}并且你可以说，亚当的创造真正意味着
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.48,1:12:52.34,English,,0,0,0,,God is Adam's creation.\N{\rChinese}神是亚当的创造物。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.66,1:12:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,God is what we created from our imagination,\N{\rChinese}神是我们从想象中创造的。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.62,1:13:02.58,English,,0,0,0,,all right? Now, you can see God is surrounded by his angels,\N{\rChinese}一切都对吗？现在，你可以看到神被他的天使包围着，
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.84,1:13:06.42,English,,0,0,0,,okay? But you take them away, and what do you have behind them?\N{\rChinese}好了？但你把它们拿走，背后你得到什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.28,1:13:11.46,English,,0,0,0,,Guys, this is a picture of the human brain, right?\N{\rChinese}伙计们，这是一幅人脑的图，没错吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.46,1:13:14.88,English,,0,0,0,,Do you see this? Okay, this is a stem, okay?\N{\rChinese}你看见这个了吗？好了，这是一根干，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.98,1:13:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,And this is the human brain, okay?\N{\rChinese}而这就是人脑，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.48,1:13:21.38,English,,0,0,0,,You take them away, and hidden behind is the human brain, right?\N{\rChinese}你把它们拿走，隐藏在后面的是人脑，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.68,1:13:23.34,English,,0,0,0,,Which means what? Which means that\N{\rChinese}哪意味着什么？哪意味着……
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.34,1:13:26.52,English,,0,0,0,,God is an emanation from our imagination,\N{\rChinese}上帝是我们想象的衍生物，
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.96,1:13:28.36,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}好了？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.16,1:13:33.68,English,,0,0,0,,Not the true God. The true God is like light itself,\N{\rChinese}不是那真神。真神就像光本身，吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.88,1:13:38.00,English,,0,0,0,,right? Love itself, okay? But this God has given us a capacity to imagine,\N{\rChinese}爱本身，好的？但这神赐给我们想象的能力，
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.14,1:13:41.04,English,,0,0,0,,so we've imagined another God to be,\N{\rChinese}于是我们想象了另一位神
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.04,1:13:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,to take place of the real God, okay?\N{\rChinese}取代真正的神，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.34,1:13:48.40,English,,0,0,0,,Do you understand? So the real God is the human imagination,\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？于是真正的神就是人类的想象，
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.22,1:13:50.78,English,,0,0,0,,the human brain, the human mind.\N{\rChinese}人类的大脑，人类的心智。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.58,1:13:53.42,English,,0,0,0,,That's what gives life to the universe, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是赋予宇宙生命的原因，吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.76,1:13:55.10,English,,0,0,0,,So this, if you think about it,\N{\rChinese}所以这件事，如果你思考一下，
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.18,1:14:00.16,English,,0,0,0,,it is a radical revolution in human intellectual history.\N{\rChinese}它是人类知识史上的一次根本革命。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.90,1:14:02.48,English,,0,0,0,,You guys, do you know where this painting is?\N{\rChinese}你们知道这幅画在哪里吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.24,1:14:08.62,English,,0,0,0,,This painting is on the top of something called the Sistine Chapel in the Vatican.\N{\rChinese}这幅画在梵蒂冈的西斯廷教堂顶部。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.38,1:14:12.88,English,,0,0,0,,It's at the Vatican. It's at the very heart of the Catholic Church.\N{\rChinese}它在梵蒂冈，正是天主教会的心脏。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.60,1:14:16.14,English,,0,0,0,,So what Darnay has been able to do\N{\rChinese}于是达纳伊所能做到的事
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.14,1:14:21.52,English,,0,0,0,,is destroy an empire peacefully for the power of poetry,\N{\rChinese}是用诗歌的力量，平静地摧毁一个帝国，
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.22,1:14:25.06,English,,0,0,0,,for subtlety, for the power of love.\N{\rChinese}用细腻与爱的力量
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.58,1:14:28.94,English,,0,0,0,,Darnay was able to influence Michelangelo, who was able to take his ideas\N{\rChinese}达纳伊能够影响米开朗，米开朗又把他的想法植入天主教会的心脏，
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.94,1:14:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,and then plant his ideas within the very heart of the Catholic Church,\N{\rChinese}随后把这些想法植入天主教会的心脏，
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.18,1:14:36.14,English,,0,0,0,,and thus reinvent the Catholic Church.\N{\rChinese}从而重新塑造了天主教会。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.36,1:14:37.80,English,,0,0,0,,That is the power of love.\N{\rChinese}那就是爱的力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.92,1:14:40.04,English,,0,0,0,,That is the power of imagination, right?\N{\rChinese}那就是想象的力量，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.70,1:14:44.78,English,,0,0,0,,Great. Okay, any questions?\N{\rChinese}好的，任何问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.48,1:14:55.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so think of some questions.\N{\rChinese}好的，先想想几个问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.60,1:15:00.40,English,,0,0,0,,Next class, we will do the Protestant Reformation, okay?\N{\rChinese}下节课我们来讲新教改革，好吗？
